text: Jeremy Solozano (born 5 October 1995) is a West Indian cricketer. He was part of the West Indies' squad for the 2014 ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup. In May 2018, he was selected to play for the Trinidad and Tobago national cricket team in the Professional Cricket League draft, ahead of the 2018–19 season. In November 2019, he was named in Trinidad and Tobago's squad for the 2019–20 Regional Super50 tournament. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:Trinidad and Tobago cricketers Category:Trinidad and Tobago representative cricketers Category:People from Arima
